==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Commiseration
<hw>Com*mis`er*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>commis⟦eacute⟧ration</ets>, fr. L. <ets>commiseratio</ets> a part
of an oration intended to excite compassion.]</ety> <def>The act of
commiserating; sorrow for the wants, afflictions, or distresses of
another; pity; compassion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And pluck <qex>commiseration</qex> of his state⟦br⟧
From brassy bosoms and rough hearts of flint.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Sympathy</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Commiserative</ent>⟦br⟧
